narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I recommend starting this course in Credit/D as a fifth class. Get a grade back and get a feel for the general flow of the course and go on from there.

If you can take this course, take this course. However, take it credit d. Professor Cleaver is wonderful and lenient, but I personally did not find her to be an easy grader. She has a lot of great life experience though, and I think if you have the opportunity to learn from someone like her, you should. The readings are also pretty great, but I think not having to stress about my grades would have made this class an even better experience.
Good course if your interested in civil rights, feminism, or African-American history. I strongly recommend. We had good discussions in class and most of the readings I genuinely enjoyed!
